social_posts.post_text: There is nothing better than waking up every day and saying “I am exactly where I ought to be.” Home is whenever I’m with these two.
My collection Angle of Attack is now available. I am offering a limited series of prints - only 10 per image. Enjoy! (link in bio)

F4U Corsairs piloted by American Naval Aviators shot down over 2100 Japanese aircraft in World War II. Powered by a Pratt and Whitney R-2800 Double Wasp 18-cylinder engine producing over 2000 horsepower, the Corsair could not only fly faster than 400 miles per hour, she was the first US single engine fighter to do so. But the gull winged design of the Corsair was not just fast. It was incredibly deadly, armed with six .50 caliber M2 Browning machine guns. It has been said that the sound the aircraft made when flying close support missions in the Pacific Theater combined with its firepower and capabilities inspired the Japanese to nickname the plane “Whistling Death.” So here they are - a group of American Naval Aviators blazing across the ocean toward the "Land of the Rising Sun." It is what I would describe as a terrifyingly beautiful sight. (Limited Prints Now Available! - link in bio)

A smooth sea never made a skilled sailor. 🏴‍☠️
Our life is a constant journey, from birth to death. The landscape changes, the people change, our needs change, but the train keeps moving. Life is the train, not the station.
In lush tropics, where palm fronds sway, paradise whispers its secrets through vibrant array.
Finding solace in nature’s grace.
Birds of paradise
Amidst the sands of time, she wonders through realms of shimmering nostalgia.
Chasing shadows
The Tetons are more than mountains; they are a source of inspiration and a reminder of the power and beauty of nature.
I’ll take the oasis of serenity over the bustling city.

As she explored her reality looking for answers she found that time is a subjective construct rather than an inherent feature of the universe. It is not an absolute or objective entity. Quantum physics and relativity challenge the linearity and universality of time, suggesting that it may be an illusion created for human comfort and understanding.
A dance of chaos and beauty.
Fear and anger have no place here
If there is magic on this planet, it is contained in water.
Wild and free
If you need me I’ll be in the 17th century
Embrace the depths, where dreams awaken and possibilities flow, for within the waters lies a world of endless wonder waiting to be explored.
The danger of adventure is worth a thousand days of ease and comfort.
Searching for the fountain of youth
Water
Florida
Paradise found in turquoise shores' gentle embrace.
Falling in love with water
Adventure is out there
